From 66b97f300d6e0b12d6159d5c944882471f6a7634 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vincenzo Grimaldi <vince.ceccarelli@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 01:22:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(design): Tesla x AWS layout migration

Tesla patterns:
- Hero is now a full-viewport (88vh) cinematic panel with vertically
  centered content over the Ken Burns reel, plus a gently bouncing
  scroll cue chevron linking to the first section

AWS patterns:
- All homepage section headers migrated from centered to left-aligned
  with a 3px accent rule on the left edge (kicker / H2 / lede)
- Feature cards get 'Learn more ->' link rows with sliding arrows,
  each routing to the relevant deep page/anchor
- Contact form migrated to console-style visible labels above every
  field with realistic placeholder examples (also an a11y win)
- 'Sign in to console' added to the primary nav (desktop) and mobile
  menu, in the exact position AWS places it

New /console route (honest sign-in affordance):
- Explains credentials ship with 2026 pilot onboarding; links to the
  simulated product preview and the pilot application
- Explicitly states no accounts exist yet; becomes the real sign-in
  when the first robots ship
